# API — Entry Points & Controllers (.acm)
> hash: sha256:8d3a2d0565d88615-3ed4204b516dbf73 | generated: 2026-03-29 | lines: ~130

## SlashCommands Catalog (506)
- **Type**: Primary user entry channel
- **File**: `.claude/commands/*.md` — each is a slash command definition
- **Purpose**: PM orchestration — every user-facing operation starts here
- **Dependencies**: agents (via Task), skills (via @include logic), rules (via @ imports)
- **Route patterns** (by prefix → functional area):
  - `sprint-*` → Sprint Management Service
  - `pbi-*` → Product Backlog Item operations
  - `spec-*`, `dev-session*` → SDD Pipeline Service
  - `arch-*`, `adr-*` → Architecture Intelligence
  - `report-*`, `ceo-*` → Executive Reporting
  - `security-*`, `a11y-*` → Security + Accessibility
  - `memory-*`, `context-*` → Memory + Context Health
  - `savia-*` → Savia platform commands
  - `flow-*` → Savia Flow practice tools
  - `school-*` → Savia School learning
  - `mcp-*` → MCP server management
  - `/codemap:*` → Agent Code Map (ACM) skill
- **Frontmatter fields**: name, description, argument-hint, allowed-tools, model(haiku|sonnet|opus), context_cost(low|medium|high)
- **UX contract**: EVERY command MUST show banner → prerequisites → progress → result (Rule #15)

## HooksPipeline
- **Type**: Automated enforcement channel (invisible to user)
- **File**: `.claude/settings.json` → hooks config
- **Purpose**: Safety and quality gates that fire on Claude Code lifecycle events
- **Dependencies**: .claude/hooks/*.sh, SAVIA_HOOK_PROFILE, lib/profile-gate.sh
- **Event mapping**:
  - `SessionStart` → `session-init.sh` (shows PAT/profile/branch status)
  - `PreToolUse(Edit)` → `ast-comprehend-hook.sh` (inject structural context before editing)
  - `PreToolUse(Bash)` → `block-credential-leak.sh`, `validate-bash-global.sh`
  - `PreToolUse(Task)` → `agent-dispatch-validate.sh` (checklist before subagent)
  - `PostToolUse(Edit|Write)` → `ast-quality-gate-hook.sh` (async quality score), `agent-trace-log.sh`
  - `Stop` → `prompt-hook-commit.sh` (semantic commit message validation)
  - `SubagentStop` → `agent-hook-premerge.sh` (pre-merge quality gate)
- **AST hooks**: comprehension(sync, PreToolUse on files ≥50 lines) + quality-gate(async, PostToolUse)

## AgentDispatch
- **Type**: Internal agent routing (invoked by commands, never directly by users)
- **File**: `.claude/agents/*.md`, `rules/domain/agents-catalog.md`, `rules/domain/assignment-matrix.md`
- **Purpose**: Route tasks to specialized subagents based on language pack and task type
- **Dependencies**: Language Pack detection, assignment-matrix.md, agent-context-budget.md
- **Routing logic** (assignment-matrix.md):
  - API REST (.NET) → dotnet-developer + test-runner
  - API REST (Java/Python/Go/Rust/PHP/Ruby/TS) → respective {lang}-developer
  - UI Angular/React → frontend-developer + frontend-test-runner
  - Mobile (iOS/Android/Flutter) → mobile-developer
  - Spec técnica → sdd-spec-writer + architect
  - Security scan → security-attacker → security-defender → security-auditor
  - Pre-commit → commit-guardian (10 checks: branch, secrets, build, tests, format, review, README, CLAUDE.md, atomicity, message)
  - Document digestion → {pdf/word/excel/pptx/visual}-digest
- **Context budgets**: Heavy(13K), Standard(8.5K), Light(4.5K), Minimal(2.2K)
- **Isolation**: developers use `isolation: worktree` for safe parallel execution

## UserProfileRouting
- **Type**: Identity & personalization channel
- **File**: `.claude/profiles/`, `.claude/rules/domain/profile-onboarding.md`
- **Purpose**: Detect user identity (human vs agent), load appropriate profile fragments, adapt Savia's voice
- **Dependencies**: active-user.md, context-map.md, role-workflows.md
- **Human flow**: active-user.md → load identity.md → greet by name → lazy-load other fragments on demand
- **Agent flow**: detect PM_CLIENT_TYPE=agent → skip greeting → structured YAML responses only
- **Role → workflow mapping**:
  - PM/Scrum Master → daily-first (sprint-status → team-workload → board-flow)
  - Tech Lead → code-focused (tech-radar → pr-pending → spec-status)
  - QA Engineer → quality-gate (qa-dashboard → pr-pending → coverage)
  - Product Owner → reporting-focused (kpi-dashboard → backlog vs capacity)
  - Developer → code-focused (my-sprint → my-focus)
  - CEO/CTO → strategic-oversight (ceo-alerts → portfolio-overview)
- **Accessibility**: `.claude/profiles/users/{slug}/accessibility.md` — screen_reader, high_contrast, cognitive_load, motor_accommodation, dyslexia_friendly, guided_work
